added.title: Various Modes of Transportation
added.description: With the other Titans away, Cyborg is forced to take a road trip with Robin.

added.title: Cool Uncles
added.description: The Titans take a trip to Wackadoodles, but Trigon makes Raven babysit her little brothers.

added.title: Monster Squad!
added.description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

added.title: Witches Brew
added.description: The Titans throw a Halloween party and invite the Justice League but the witches brew Robin creates has side effects.

added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: Costume Contest
added.description: Sick of losing the costume contest to the Hive Five every year, the Titans hatch a scheme to win.

added.title: Scary Figure Dance
added.description: The Titans' Halloween party is interupted by the Hive Five robbing a candy factory.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.

added.title: Campfire Stories
added.description: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

added.title: Little Buddies
added.description: Cyborg wants Pain Bot to be his "little buddy" but is the destructive robot too dangerous to be a sidekick?

added.title: Dreams
added.description: A glimpse inside each Titan's dream world.

added.title: Real Magic
added.description: Robin dabbles with magic, ignoring Raven's warning that he will anger the magic god.

added.title: The Curse of Elmore
added.description: When Gumball's schoolfriend Leslie finds an old video tape, the creepy mystery of Elmore's ghostly past unfolds. Featuring spooky and hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: The Sucker
added.description: Gumball spends the day with Bomb Kid, who has decided Gumball is the perfect target for him and his friends to play pranks on. However he soon learns that Gumball is so gullible that pranks bounce off him.

added.title: The Vegging
added.description: Gumball and Darwin want to have a lazy day on the sofa, and have come up with various tricks to stop themselves having to move. Gradually more and more people arrive, seemingly to get them to move, until finally they realize that if they have to move, they'll do it in the laziest way possible.

added.title: The Shippening
added.description: When people that barely know each other start falling in love, Gumball thinks he knows who's behind it. He rushes to Sarah's house and finds her writing in a magic notebook that turns everything in it into reality. When everything in Elmore gets crazier and crazier there's only one thing for it: they have to write their way out.

added.title: The Spinoffs
added.description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob, each one is worse than the last.

added.title: The Stink
added.description: Gumball decides to put Mr. Small's eco-friendly principles to the test but it doesn't quite go as planned. Mr. Small disappears after deciding to leave the modern world behind. But on the plus side they discover that the Great Stink-Ape of Elmore Woods is definitely not extinct.

added.title: The Silence
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin's conversation dries up, they worry that their friendship is coming to an end. They try to find ways to get the conversation flowing again, but nothing seems to work. Maybe they have just grown apart?

added.title: The Heart
added.description: When Mr. Robinson accidentally let slip how little he cares for Gumball and Darwin, they react by giving him the cold shoulder.  Surprisingly Mr. Robinson misses them and tries to win back their friendship. After a few failed attempts, Gumball and Darwin realize that Mr. Robinson's heart is protecting him, so they give it an intense affection overload.

added.title: The Slide
added.description: A chance encounter with the woman of his dreams inspires Rocky to stop living life online and find love with the help of the latest dating app. Gumball and Darwin try to help Rocky through the tricky world of online romance. In the race to find Rocky's dream girl, they discover people can forgive almost anything when you tell them you're acting in the name of love.

added.title: The Stars
added.description: When Dad gives Larry's hairdresser a bad review for saying he's bald, he gets offered a free haircut. This inspires Gumball and Darwin to go on a reviewing spree across town, forcing Larry to give them stuff with the threat of a bad review. Just because the customer is always right doesn't mean that what they're doing isn't wrong.

added.title: The Sorcerer
added.description: Gumball refuses to accept he is the only kid at school that doesn't have special powers. He convinces Mrs. Jotunheim, Hector's mom, to take him on as his apprentice but she soon learns leaving Gumball unsupervised around magic is a big mistake.

added.title: The Weirdo
added.description: When they see the school bullies making fun of Sussie, Gumball and Darwin decide to try and help her act less weird. They carefully observe her behavior and decide that the only thing they have to change is absolutely everything.

added.title: The Origins
added.description: When Mom and Dad struggle to keep hyperactive, toddler-aged Gumball from trashing the house and exhausting them, they decide to buy him a pet. It works, but there's a problem: every goldfish they get him is short-lived, and inevitably ends up being flushed down the toilet.

added.title: The Origins Part 2
added.description: Via the sewers, Darwin finds himself flushed out to sea. He is terrified but determined to make his way back to the Wattersons. However, a fish can't get very far on land so Darwin will have to do millions of years of evolution in a matter of hours if he's going to get home safe and sound.

added.title: Trick or Creek
added.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: While taking refuge from the chilly Creek, Craig and his friends decide to hangout at his house until lunch time!

added.title: Breaking the Ice
added.description: While searching a once unreachable part of the Creek, Craig gets stranded with his longtime rival, Wildernessa!

added.title: Winter Creeklympics
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP try their luck at winning Gold in their first ever, Winter Creeklympics!

added.title: Welcome to Creek Street
added.description: Craig and his friends create their own neighborhood in the snow!

added.title: Fan or Foe
added.description: When Elder Con comes to the Creek, Craig, Kelsey and JP each have a con experience they'll never forget.

added.title: New Jersey
added.description: After donning a brand new Jersey, JP is recruited by the Hockey Kids! The only way to get JP back is for Craig and Kelsey to hit the ice!

added.title: The Sunflower
added.description: Our Trio makes a new friend in the Creek, but when her pet befalls a tragic fate, Kelsey believes she knows how to help.

added.title: Craig World
added.description: Craig creates an amusement park in the Creek! But when things start to get stale, he vows to make it bigger and better, no matter what it takes!

added.title: Camper on the Run
added.description: A runaway from a summer camp ends up at the Stump, but Craig suspects her story may not be what it seems.

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Crisis at Elder Rock
added.description: Tragedy strikes the Creek when the Elders get trapped under Elder Rock, and it's up to Craig, Kelsey and JP to rescue them.

added.title: Kelsey the Worthy
added.description: When Kelsey demolishes a wall at Craig's house, her father takes away her sword. So she enlists Craig and JP to help prove to her father that she's still worthy.

added.title: Ghoul Spirit
added.description: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.

added.title: Duncan Carving
added.description: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

added.title: Double Oh Beth
added.description: With most of the class already gone for spring break, a nefarious villain infiltrates the school. Luckily a sleeper agent has been lying in wait. Hold on... it's BETH?!? Oh boy.

added.title: Duncan Duty
added.description: When Duncan realizes Chef is getting kids to tattle on him in return for chocolate milk he sees an opportunity.

added.title: Encore'tney
added.description: When Courtney turns to a magical datebook to help her achieve perfection, she's trapped in a never ending loop until a friend teaches her a valuable lesson.

added.title: Life of Pie
added.description: When Izzy, Jude and Owen accidentally bring a pizza to life they do everything they can to help him find a new purpose in life other than being eaten.

added.title: AbaracaDuncan
added.description: When a magic trick goes sideways, Duncan makes a great escape and Harold becomes the target of a Sorcerer Hunt!

added.title: Shock & AWW
added.description: When Courtney gets the old, gross daycare carpet replaced with a new one, the resulting static electricity has unexpected consequences.

added.title: School District 9
added.description: When a career predicting machine tells Owen he has no skills to offer the world, Owen finds a way to prove the machine wrong in the most Owen way possible.

added.title: The A-Bok-Bok-Bokalypse
added.description: When chicken pox sweeps through the school, the kids visit the Chicken Queen to apologize for past misdeeds and hopefully to procure an antidote, before it's too late!

added.title: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
added.description: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

added.title: Lords of Ghost Town
added.description: When V&V recruit a ghost to scare away a bully, they end up messing with the realm of the dead, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 3: La Llorona
added.description: When Val sets out to get a little privacy in the woods, Vic is bent on pranking his unsuspecting brother,  that is, until Val goes missing.

added.title: Cenote Seekers
added.description: When Vic and Val are running too late to get a ride from Xochi to a fun water park cenote on a particularly hot day, they instead take their bikes. But they wind up lost in the desert and start to hallucinate while blaming each other for getting into this mess.

added.title: My Thirsty Little Monster
added.description: When Valentino discovers Victor has been hiding a baby vampire bat in the house, Victor must convince his brother that he can handle having a pet.

added.title: La Planchada
added.description: When Vic gets the chicken pox and is forbidden from playing in a tag tournament, he summons a mythical ghost nurse to cure him.

added.title: Tez Breaks Bread
added.description: When Tez returns to town and invites Chata and the boys to a dinner party, she insists they attend so Victor and Valentino set out to expose him as the evil magician he truly is.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 1
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 2
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SweetJustice Part 3
added.description: When six ordinary girls meet and discover that they each have extraordinary powers, they decide to join forces to take on one of Metropolis's most sinister villains.

added.title: #SoulSisters Part 1
added.description: The girls must track down Katana, a mysterious warrior who's stealing the souls of Metropolis's villains. Meanwhile, Diana's new friend Tatsu is a perfect match for her in every way, but may have a connection to Katana.

added.title: #SoulSisters Part 2
added.description: The girls must track down Katana, a mysterious warrior who's stealing the souls of Metropolis's villains. Meanwhile, Diana's new friend Tatsu is a perfect match for her in every way, but may have a connection to Katana.

added.title: Charlie's Halloween Thing 2
added.description: Charlie tells some scary stories featuring the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Charlie's Halloween Thing
added.description: Charlie hosts an evening of spooky stories starring the Bears.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Chicken and Waffles
added.description: Panda needs to meet his brothers at the most exclusive restaurant in town. But when he loses his contacts lenses and can't see, Panda needs Charlie's help to get him into the city.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: Patty's Law
added.description: If found guilty of breaking Patty's Law, Apple and Onion face grave punishment but they have a more pressing concern; looking after their dear, sickly Falafel.

added.title: The Eater
added.description: It's Halloween and Apple's not feeling quite right. He takes Onion into the dark depths to find out why.

added.title: Ferekh
added.description: Apple and Onion are put in charge of Falafel's beloved rooster but it turns out that other parties have a vested interest in it too.

added.title: Falafel's Glory
added.description: Apple and Onion must recruit the help of retired quiz master Falafel if they are to not starve.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Burger's roommate is not only a problem for him, but for Apple and Onion who need Burger's help for something else.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Having finally saved up and aquired an expensive toy race track, Apple and Onion are faced with one problem- there is no time to play with it.

added.title: Walking on the Ceiling
added.description: Apple's curiosity of what it would be like to walk upside down like a spider should be ignored and given no further thought. It is not.

added.title: Panamanian Night Monkey
added.description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

added.title: Nothing Can Stop Us
added.description: Hot Dog has the audition of his life but he is missing something crucial. Apple and Onion are tasked with bringing it to him and they are adamant that nothing will stand in their way.

added.title: Champion
added.description: Stuck with a problematic pet, Apple and Onion need to somehow find a way to get their lives back.

added.title: Roundabout Part 2
added.description: Forever Knight, with an over-clocked Time Machine in his grasp and a group of super- baddies by his side, is close to conquering all of history, but a certain hero with a team of 10 aliens on his side has other plans— foiling Forever Knight at every twist and turn in time!

added.title: Beware the Scare-Crow
added.description: During a visit to the farm of Penny Bennyson's grandfather, Team Tennyson is constantly haunted by a Scare-Crow that's come to life, but when Ben discovers that Aristocrow is behind it all, our hero must defeat Aristocrow's master, the steam-powered Steam Smythe, if he is to save his cousin's farm!

added.title: And Xingo Was His Name-O
added.description: When a new Xingo app mysteriously appears on Gwen's tablet, Ben can't help himself and activates it despite his cousin's disapproval, springing a trap that transports Ben in the animated world and Xingo back in the real world. It's the ol' switcheroo!

added.title: Xingo Nation
added.description: Kevin 11 gives Xingo a power up - setting him loose to wreak havoc on other TV shows - and it is up to Ben to stop them both.

added.title: Heat of the Moment
added.description: After Ben easily dispatches the Weatherheads, Team Tennyson travels to a ski resort for some fun in the snow but when Ben runs into the Weatherheads yet again, this time they are a force to reckon with, now that Kevin 11 has used his Bootleg powers to unlock their emotional controls!

added.title: A Sticky Situation
added.description: All Ben wants to do is stop Queen Bee from robbing a bank, but when Kevin shows up to try and be the hero and take all the glory himself, Ben will need to save the day twice or end up in hot honey.

added.title: You Remind Me of Someone
added.description: Ben and Gwen look for the infamous Bojamboo (the Bigfoot of the South) and discover that it's actually the Forgeti, at the same time as Kevin 11, but when Ben and Kevin are blasted with the Forgeti's forgetfulness mist, they reverse roles and it's up to Gwen and Max to restore them back to normal.

added.title: Steam Fight at the OK Corral
added.description: When Kevin convinces Steam Smythe to adopt a modern approach in fighting Ben, our young hero must resort to old-fashioned thinking to save the day.

added.title: I Don't Like You
added.description: Ben and Gwen's social media battle with Kevin 11 quickly escalates into an all-out war in real life.

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Clown College
added.description: While tailgating at a State U. homecoming football game, Ben teams up with Grandpa Max's old college buddies to keep the crazy clown Zombozo from robbing the stadium blind at halftime.

added.title: Scared Silly
added.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

added.title: Memory Mayhem
added.description: Frankie tries to discover more about the mysterious rock that bought them to their new home, with the help of an entity called The Head.

added.title: Developing Dilemna
added.description: Frankie lets Elliott get a pet, which doesn't go down well with their new neighbor.

added.title: Nevin's Cocoon
added.description: After a beautiful statue makes Nevin self-conscious about his own looks, Seth helps seal Nevin in a cocoon so that he may turn into a beautiful butterfly.

added.title: Cool Kids
added.description: When Pascal becomes obsessed with a group of cool kids, Seth promises to use his science skills to help Pascal become cool. But is coolness as cool as it seems?

added.title: Mermove Out
added.description: Seth is having a hard time sharing a room with messy Pascal and needs a change. But instead of being honest about the situation, Seth makes Pascal a mermaid tail so that his brother can finally move out - into the ocean!

added.title: Happy Birthday Nancy
added.description: Seth wants his mom to have the best birthday ever, so he creates his own currency in order to buy her an expensive gift. But he learns a little too late that counterfeiting is a crime, putting Nancy's birthday at risk of being ruined.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Reunited
added.description: Steven brings everyone together for a special reunion.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: With many changes going on in his life, Steven tries to find his place in the world.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

added.title: It Could've Been Great
added.description: The Gems take a trip to the moon.

added.title: Message Received
added.description: Steven has doubts about believing in everyone.

added.title: Log Date 7 15 2
added.description: Steven sneaks a listen to a friend's audio diary.

added.title: Super Watermelon Island
added.description: Steven finds out what happened to all those sentient watermelons he created.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Catch and Release
added.description: We finally see inside Steven's bathroom.

added.title: Back to the Barn
added.description: Steven and the Gems head back to the family barn to build some robots.

added.title: Horror Club
added.description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

added.title: Panthro Plagiarized!
added.description: Vultureman has got a brand new invention but there's one big problem: he stole the idea from Panthro! Oh, also Vultureman is using his invention to take over Third Earth. So, there are two big problems.

added.title: Warrior Maiden Invasion
added.description: Third Earth is being overrun by super tough, super buff Warrior Maidens and it looks like the ThunderCats are next on their hit list! It's gonna be up to the ThunderKittens to save the day even though the kittens are so small and the Warrior Maidens are so big.

added.title: Lost Sword
added.description: Lion-O is reminded that he needs to plug the Sword of Omens into the Cats' Lair each night or else the base will run out of power. That's fine, it's not like Lion-O's going to accidentally lose the sword or anything. Right?

added.title: The Horror of Hook Mountain
added.description: Tygra takes Lion-O climbing up the peak of Hook Mountain to teach him a lesson about trust. But when they get trapped by a snowstorm and take refuge in a creepy cabin owned by the creepy Snowman - it's Tygra's ability to the trust that's gonna be tested.

added.title: ThunderSlobs
added.description: Tygra's feeling unappreciated by the other ThunderCats so he starts hanging out with Mumm-Ra and cleaning his Black Pyramid?! Whaaaaaaat?

added.title: Queen of the Munce
added.description: Jay, Nya and Lloyd are led deep into the Mines of Shintaro by Murt, who brings them back to the Munce "Home- Cave" - a settlement deep in the mountain. There, complications arise when they meet the Munce Queen, Murtessa, who takes a liking to Jay.

added.title: Trial By Mino
added.description: Separated from the others, Kai and Zane discover a party of Geckles who suspect them of being in league with the Skull Sorcerer, and bring them before their leader, Chancellor Gulch, who subjects them to a "Trial-By-Mino."

added.title: The Skull Sorcerer
added.description: Separated from the others, Cole must trust his instincts and make the right choices to find his way to the surface to alert King Vangelis of the dangerous Skull Sorcerer.

added.title: The Real Fall!
added.description: An entire episode chronicles the ninja's most bizarre adventure yet: in which Cole, Princess Vania and Master Wu fall down a seemingly endless tunnel, into the bowels of Shintaro Mountain.

added.title: Dungeon Party
added.description: Having survived their fall into the mountain, Cole, Wu and Princess Vania befriend a motley group of survivors, called the Lowly, and are told the story of how they too ended up at "Rock-Bottom."

added.title: I Love You Mao Mao
added.description: An explosive loner and his slacker best friend are waylaid from their journey into legend, only to find that their story is just beginning.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Not Impressed
added.description: When a Sweetypie isn't impressed with the sheriff dept's antics, our three heroes try everything to win him over.

added.title: Enemy Mime
added.description: When the Sheriff's Dept fights a monster that copies their every move, they'll have to find a way to fight without fighting.

added.title: Bao Bao's Revenge
added.description: When Mao Mao's old partner threatens the kingdom, his friends will need to learn about his past in order to protect the present.

added.title: All By Mao Self
added.description: Mao Mao's desire to be a legend drives him to keep topping himself. But how much is enough?

added.title: Scooby-Doo! Shaggy's Showdown
added.description: Join Scooby-Doo and the gang for a frightfully wacky ride in this all-new original movie as they visit the Crazy Q Dude Ranch. But before they can strap on their spurs, the ghost of the scalawag outlaw Dapper Jack rides into town to rattle the gang and the other guests. Now, it's up to the mystery-loving posse to round up the dreadful critter and save the ranch!

added.title: Scooby-Doo & Batman: The Brave and the Bold
added.description: The ultimate crime-solving combination reunites when Batman joins the Mystery Inc. gang to catch a gaggle of villains wreaking havoc. Super sleuths Scooby-Doo, Shaggy, Fred, Daphne and Velma join forces with Gotham City's greatest detective, Batman, when they discover villains from both of their respective rogues' galleries have also combined efforts to terrorize the city. With Scooby snacks in tow, the crime-fighting teams encounter classic Batman foes and allies along with a bevy of fiends from Scooby-Doo lore. As always, you won't know who the ultimate villain is until those meddling kids pull off the mask!

added.title: Scooby-Doo! and the Curse of the 13th Ghost
added.description: After Mystery Inc. bumble a case and nab an innocent man, they're forced into early retirement from solving crime. But it doesn't take long before their old friend Vincent Van Ghoul needs help, and pulls the team right back into action. It all started one Summer when Scooby-Doo, Shaggy and Daphne secretly hunted down 12 of the world's spookiest ghosts, but failed to catch the most evil one of all… the 13th ghost. With the 13th ghost on the loose, the gang will have to look past their hidden secrets and settle some unfinished business. Bundle up and get ready for the icy slopes of the Himalayan mountains, chilling car chases, crystal balls and spine-tingling spells in this terrifyingly fun original movie!

added.title: Scooby-Doo and the Gourmet Ghost
added.description: Pull up a chair, tuck in that napkin, and get ready for a 5-star meal of mystery with Scooby-Doo and the gang, as we hit the road to visit the Rocky Harbor Culinary Resort to meet Fred's uncle, world-famous chef Bobby Flay. Mystery Inc. quickly learns that this state-of-the-art cooking resort isn't all steak and potatoes after they find out about the legend of the Red Ghost, and the unsolved disappearance of Bobby Flay's great ancestor chef. When the mysterious Red Ghost returns in disastrous fashion to haunt the inn, the gang teams up with Bobby and his culinary pal Giada De Laurentiis, to dig in for clues and serve up justice. Will history repeat itself and find another world-famous chef missing?

added.title: Scooby-Doo! The Sword and the Scoob
added.description: Scooby and the gang go on a trip to England to trace Shaggy's family roots, where they suddenly find themselves in the Middle Ages and meet the legendary King Arthur and his noble knights.

added.title: Scooby-Doo! and WWE: Curse of the Speed Demon
added.description: Scooby and the gang stumble upon a menacing phantom at an off-road racing competition. With the help of some WWE superstars, they try to save the race before it's too late.

added.title: Scooby-Doo! and Kiss Rock and Roll Mystery
added.description: When a ghoul begins to terrorize an amusement park, the Mystery Inc. gang come head to head with the legendary rock group, KISS, who claim they're also there to solve the mystery. Now the two groups must learn to work together as the clues lead them on a cosmic journey to another dimension.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: The Scratch Pack
added.description: Axel and the team must run damage control after a loose spark of Minergy accidentally turns Zoe's old toys - a set of cute squishy kittens - into a pack of snarling beasts.

added.title: Knockout
added.description: Axel and the team juggle not waking Uncle Andrew from his nap and stopping Orangutank from stealing Andrew's latest invention: the Knockout Box!

added.title: Sarge in Charge
added.description: Axel and the team must rescue Sarge Charge from a solo mission in the backyard, which Orangutank has turned into his own personal heart of darkness.

added.title: The Mysterious Boy/A New Power
added.description: The Mysterious Boy: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. With the Bakugan boom, brawling has been reinvented as a sporting game. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event./A New Power: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl! Dan and Drago go head to head with the outsides to get to the bottom of it. Outmatched by their opponent, Dan and Drago get a little help from a new powerful weapon - Baku-Gear.

added.title: Baku-Gear/Bakugan Rock!
added.description: Baku-Gear: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?/Bakugan Rock!: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

added.title: Brawler Headhunting/Lightning's Entrance Exam
added.description: Brawler Headhunting: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five. /Lightning's Entrance Exam: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

added.title: Trouble Busters!/French Fry Wars
added.description: Trouble Busters!: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it./French Fry Wars: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

added.title: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call/Phantom Thief Ajit
added.description: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves./Phantom Thief Ajit: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

added.title: Scary Tales 2
added.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

added.title: The Escape Room of Doom
added.description: The gang infiltrate an escape room game center to thwart Score Creeper, but their former foe claims he only works there to pay the bills.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Rainbow Race
added.description: Sadness levels have hit an all-time low in Frowntown. In an attempt to cheer up the citizens of the town, Unikitty and the gang load a rainbow into a tanker truck with the intention of releasing it over Frowntown. Now they must avoid the marauding Master Frown in his monster truck, to succeed.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: A super-grumpy volcano appears in the kingdom, so Unikitty takes the gang on an epic quest to cheer it up with one of FeeBee's flowers before it erupts and destroys the kingdom.

added.title: Late Night Talky Time
added.description: The moon is bored of taking the nightshift, since everyone's always asleep. So Unikitty leads the gang in putting on an over-the-top late night talk show to keep the moon occupied.

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: Tasty Heist
added.description: Richard's prepared one of the tastiest desserts ever, but he's locked it up tight until the friends have their boring dinner. This will not stand. Unikitty organizes a heist, assembling the friends as a crack team to get in, get out, and eat that tasty snack without Richard knowing. But this heist has hiccups. Can the friends take the cake?

added.title: Big Pup, Little Problem
added.description: After a mishap in the lab, everyone in the castle- except for Puppycorn- is shrunk to tiny size! Puppycorn thinks it's cool. His friends are like living action figures! So he begins playing with them in imaginary adventures. Unikitty and the others think being miniature and playing with Puppycorn is surprisingly fun, but PC has a habit of accidentally breaking his toys, and it's soon clear the gang will have to make a daring, tiny escape back to the lab before Puppycorn loves them to pieces!

added.title: Scary Tales
added.description: During the gang's Halloween party, Unikitty discovers Brick isn't scared of anything! To get him in the holiday spirit, the gang tell their own ideas of what a spooky story is, hoping to scare the emotionless Rick for once, with each tale even scarier (and sillier) than the last!

added.title: We Are Heroes
added.description: KO struggles with his upgraded role as a member of the hero team.

added.title: Let's Meet Sonic
added.description: When world class hero SONIC THE HEDGEHOG visits the plaza, he teams up with KO to save the day.

added.title: TKO Rules!
added.description: KO and TKO decide to swap places for the day.

added.title: K.O. vs Fink
added.description: When Fink taunts KO for being a momma's boy, he grapples with newfound insecurity about it.

added.title: Planet X
added.description: When Rad returns to his home planet, he learns a shocking truth about alien society.

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: Crossover Nexus
added.description: When KO finds himself trapped inside an mysterious place, he encounters other Cartoon Network Heroes and they band together to escape.

added.title: All in the Villainy
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid are confused to find the villains are more interested in battling each other than them.

added.title: Monster Party
added.description: Enid is faced with a choice when her old friends from Ghoul School show up.

added.title: Dark Plaza
added.description: KO and the heroes of the Plaza fight to save Lakewood Plaza Turbo with everything on the line.

added.title: We Got Hacked
added.description: Dendy helps KO, Enid and Rad stop a glitch that threatens to take over the bodega.

added.title: Villains' Night Out
added.description: Lord Boxman forces his way into an exclusive Villains party.

added.title: Villains' Night In
added.description: While Boxman and Venomous are out, Fink is reluctantly babysat by Darrell and Shannon.

added.title: Mystery Science Fair 201X
added.description: KO helps Dendy with her science fair project.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
added.description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
added.description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.

added.title: Witch's Crew
added.description: On Halloween Night, Morbucks summons a monster that she didn't expect.

added.title: Midnight at the Mayor's Mansion
added.description: When the Mayor's mansion is stalked by a vicious, ghostly monster, he calls the Powerpuff Girls for help.

added.title: Man Up 3: The Good, the Bad, and the Manly
added.description: After Bubbles gets blasted with Man Boy's beard ray, she wreaks havoc in the most manly and adorable way possible.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: Odd Bubbles Out
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn visits, Bubbles becomes jealous of his new friend.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: Rainy Day
added.description: The girls get into trouble when left to entertain themselves on a rainy day.

added.title: The Squashening
added.description: To escape a monster, the girls have to tell him a scary story.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
added.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: Max's Monster
added.description: Grandpa Max's old Plumber partner, Phil, seeks Max's help to tame the monster within. (Introducing new Ben alien, Buzzshock; Re-introducing old Ben alien, Benvicktor.)

added.title: Something Zombozo This Way Comes
added.description: Ben and Rook must stop Zombozo and the Circus Freaks from turning everyone in Bellwood into zombie clowns!

added.title: Rad Monster Party
added.description: Ben and Rook enlist the help of intergalactic smuggler Rad Dudesman to fly them through the Anur System, the home of the monstrous aliens!

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: A New Dawn
added.description: The Time War brings Ben, Rook, and George Washington together to battle an alien conqueror.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 1
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo Parte 2
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
added.description: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

added.title: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
added.description: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park V
added.description: The fifth installment of Terror Tales finds Benson trying to spice up the park's annual Halloween party by renting a wish making machine.

added.title: Blank Eyed Girl
added.description: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

added.title: Los Vegetales
added.description: Gumball y Darwin solo quieren holgazanear todo el día, pero terminan teniendo que salvar al resto de la familia.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park IV
added.description: The park guys try to keep Muscle Man awake with scary stories on a long drive so that they can meet his mom.

added.title: El Corazon
added.description: El señor Robinson intenta recuperar la amistad de Gumball y Darwin y falla una y otra vez.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Equipo Monstruo
added.description: Los Titanes quieren convertirse en los mejores del pueblo a la hora de pedir dulces o trucos en Halloween y, para ello, Raven lanza un hechizo que los convierte en monstruos reales.

added.title: Mystery Dungeon
added.description: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.

added.title: La pregunta
added.description: Steven les muestra a unas gemas citadinas cómo vivían los vaqueros.

added.title: Reunificados
added.description: Steven reúne a todos para un evento especial.

added.title: Familiar
added.description: Con tantos cambios en su vida, Steven intenta encontrar su lugar en el mundo.

added.title: Escapismo
added.description: Steven usa sus poderes psíquicos para conseguir ayuda.

added.title: Costume Crisis
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes improvements to a kid's Halloween costume.

added.title: El Espantoso Segundo Especial de Halloween de Charlie
added.description: Charlie cuenta algunas historias de miedo protagonizadas por los Osos y sus amigos.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park III
added.description: Each of the park guys want to win a bet by telling the scariest story at a Halloween party.

added.title: A Nightmare on Aberdale Street: Balance's Revenge
added.description: In this Halloween adventure, Clarence uses a special jack-o-lantern to enter the world of people's dreams. He discovers that something mysterious is causing his friends to have nightmares, and Clarence needs to stop it!

added.title: Concurso de Disfraces
added.description: Hartos de que los Hive Five les ganen en el concurso de disfraces, los Titanes elaboran un plan para ganar.

added.title: No One Can Hear You
added.description: Where are the citizens of Ooo?

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park II
added.description: The park can be a very scary place at night.

added.title: Las historias de Halloween de Charlie
added.description: Charlie es el presentador de unas historias de terror protagonizadas por los Osos.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park
added.description: The park can be a very scary place at night.

added.title: Campista Profuga
added.description: Una fugitiva de un campamento de verano termina en el Tronco, pero Craig sospecha que su historia puede no ser lo que parece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Fool Moon
added.description: Strange things start happening when Uncle Grandpa installs a moon roof in the RV.

added.title: Bewitched, Bothered and Bothered Some More!
added.description: Flonk hires the Warriors to make Witch Way change his brother Helmut from a frog back to human.

added.title: King of the Zombeez
added.description: Frostferatu hires the Warriors to rid his castle of Zombeez when Neddy and a power mad zombie-bee queen take over.

added.title: Cuentos de miedo 2
added.description: Es Halloween de nuevo y la banda trata de contar aterradoras historias a un grupo de niños que piden dulces.

added.title: Juicio de Mino
added.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

added.title: El Hechicero Calavera
added.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Fiesta en el Calabozo
added.description: Cole, Wu y la Princesa Vania conocen a un grupo de sobrevivientes llamados los de abajo, ellos cuentan cómo terminaron en "Lo más profundo".

added.title: La Gran Caida
added.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

added.title: Crisis en la roca de Ancianos
added.description: Una tragedia azota al Arroyo cuando los Ancianos quedan atrapados bajo la Roca Anciana. Ahora Craig, Kelsey y JP deben rescatarlos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Reina de los Munces
added.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

added.title: Kelsey la merecedora
added.description: Cuando Kelsey demuele una pared de la casa de Craig, su padre le quita la espada. Por eso, Kelsey les pide ayuda a Craig y a JP para que le demuestren a su padre que aún la merece.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Suciedad
added.description: A Ben le encargan la tarea de limpiar la Chatarra, pero cuando, engañado por los viles villanos Fly Guys, permite que se lo roben, debe perseguirlos antes de que fabriquen una larva monstruosa imparable con un objetivo claro: destruir Las Vegas.

added.title: What a Night for a Dark Knight!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang come to Gotham City to visit Alfred Pennyworth, they stumble into a dangerous mystery! Alfred's been kidnapped by the Man-Bat! Batman is on the case and he does not want any help from our meddling kids.

added.title: Mushroom Menace
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

added.title: Mystery 101
added.description: Velma's got an interview at the prestigious Kingston University, the most selective school in the country. The only catch? The dean wants her and the rest of the Scooby gang to figure out why the ghost of Elias Kingston, the school's founder, is haunting Kingston's book-filled halls!

added.title: Beware the Beast from Below
added.description: Crystal Cove may be the most haunted town in the world but that doesn't stop Scooby and the gang from trying to prove that most of its most famous tourist attractions were fakes, much to the anger and dwindling profits of their parents. But when a radioactive barrel is accidentally opened releasing a hideous sewer beast that cocoons its victims in frozen yogurt, their mystery-solving skills are put to the test. After all, what could a sewer beast, a delicious edible dessert, underground caves and shrimping boats made of balloons possibly have in common? I'll give you a little hint - the local bank.

added.title: What a Night for a Knight
added.description: Scooby-Doo and Shaggy stumble across a lone suit of black armor and embark on a quest to find the artifact's missing owner.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Segunda parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 2 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: Elementary, My Dear Shaggy!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are taking a tour of merry old London, they run afoul of horrible screaming skulls of English legend! They team up with an eccentric man who claims to be none other than Sherlock Holmes. Of course, he can't be the real thing, can he?

added.title: Game of Chicken
added.description: Fred gets a call for help from Chuck, his daredevil of a best friend, leading the gang on a rescue mission deep in the caverns of an ancient civilization. Once there, they learn of the real mystery: the ghost of the Tribal Warrior still protects the cavern from outsiders!

added.title: The Creeping Creatures
added.description: A long time ago, there was a town called Gatorburg, where gators flowed wild and free and people got rich. Now, it's a ghost town. Gators are all dried up. But when Scooby and the gang receive an imitation Gatorburg purse, they decide to see for themselves if the gators really are gone. Forced to stay overnight when someone steals the engine to the Mystery Machine, they soon discover that gators have indeed returned - only these have comb-overs, walk on two legs and don't like visitors.

added.title: A Clue for Scooby-Doo
added.description: Scooby and the gang become mixed up in a mystery when he surfs into what appears to be the ghost of Captain Cutler.

added.title: #LaDulceJusticia - Tercera parte
added.description: Cuando seis chicas comunes y corrientes descubren que cada una tiene un poder extraordinario diferente, deciden unir fuerzas para derrotar a algunos de los villanos más siniestros de Metrópolis en la parte 3 del episodio estreno.
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El Lider Del Ring
added.description: Cuando Ben tiene una racha ganadora en un videojuego, se le ocurre una idea para ganar un partido real de lucha, hasta que un luchador intimidante decide convertirlo en un verdadero desafío.

added.title: A Mystery Solving Gang Divided!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang travel to Chambersburg, a battlefield near Gettysburg, to investigate the mysterious appearance of ghost zombie Civil War soldiers and come face to face with a rival mystery solving gang, the Funky Phantom crew. The rivalry between the two gangs gets so out of hand that it threatens to keep either group from solving the mystery, until the ghost of Abraham Lincoln appears and tries to get them focused.

added.title: All Paws on Deck
added.description: The gang climb aboard the cruise ship run by Fred's cousin, despite Velma's strong dislike of water. But a water phobia is the least of their problems when a terrifying sea monster attacks the ship!

added.title: The Secret of the Ghost Rig
added.description: A mysterious ghost trucker is terrorizing Crystal Cove. Add to that all the doorknobs have begun to disappear from around town, someone has hidden a priceless diamond and Fred's dad, the Mayor, is up for re-election against a guy named Avocados. Scooby and the gang have their hands full. Oh, and did we mention Daphne has been set-up on a blind date with a pinhead named Rung Ladderton, who - wait for it - sells ladders for a living.

added.title: Hassle in the Castle
added.description: The sleuths shipwreck on a deserted island and explore a haunted castle.

added.title: Revenge of the Swamp Monster!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. gang meet up with basketball legend and bowling aficionado Chris Paul at a golf tournament fundraiser held in Florida. Shaggy's come to caddy for Mr. Paul and help him with this game so the Assist King can save a local school from going under. But, when a horrible Swamp Monster attacks trying to destroy the charity event, our heroes and Mr. Paul must finish the tournament and save the school, and possibly their own lives!

added.title: Poodle Justice
added.description: It's Scooby's dream come true as the gang visits the set of his favorite TV show and he meets the star, his celebrity crush, a dog actress who plays a detective on the screen. Now all Scooby has to do is work up the courage to actually talk to her while also solving the mystery of the monstrous gargoyle attacking the production!

added.title: Revenge of the Man Crab
added.description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

added.title: Mine Your Own Business
added.description: The gang explores a mining town and investigate a phantom miner, who's driving the business away from a nearby dude ranch.

added.title: Peebles' Pet Shop of Terrible Terrors!
added.description: Scooby and the Mystery Inc. gang meet Wanda Sykes, who is helping save a bunch of cute, fuzzy animals up for adoption in a large pet supply store. When a crazy monster egg hatches a monster in the pet store's back room, our heroes and Wanda must not only save the store and the animals, but their own lives!

added.title: Grand Scam
added.description: Shaggy takes the Gang to the Minor League Baseball stadium of his youth only to learn that it's about to be shut down because a Ghostly Baseball Player is scaring away the fans and the team! Shaggy puts aside his cowardly ways to saves his home team but will Scooby stand by his, now not so scared, pal?

added.title: The Song of Mystery
added.description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

added.title: Decoy for a Dognapper
added.description: Scooby impersonates a prize-winning Great Dane to catch whoever is stealing show dogs.

added.title: Flirty Phantom
added.description: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas!

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Sitter
added.description: Gus and Pizza Steve have plans to go out for the night, but UG can't be left alone in the RV, so they need a babysitter.  But when none are available, they turn to UG to babysit himself.

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Time Share
added.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: Under a Red Sun
added.description: Steppenwolf "boom tubes" Superman to a planet with a red sun in order to make the Man of Steel powerless. Somehow Batman and Big Barda have to locate the planet before Superman is destroyed.

added.title: Escuela De Payasos
added.description: Mientras Ben disfruta en el estacionamiento a la salida de un partido de fútbol americano de ex estudiantes de la Universidad de State, se alía con los antiguos compañeros del Abuelo Max para impedir que Zombozo, un payaso demente, le robe a todo el público durante el entretiempo.

added.title: Afraid of the Dark
added.description: When UG helps a little girl who is afraid of the dark, he convinces her there's nothing to be afraid of but their imaginations.  But when their imaginations prove to be pretty terrifying, they go on a quest to turn on the lights.

added.title: Trick or Threat
added.description: Four kids in Justice League costumes are trick or treating on Halloween when they investigate a spooky house. As dangers befalls them inside, they come to realize that maybe they're not kids at all, but real Justice Leaguers under a spell.

added.title: Little Sword of Horrors
added.description: Prohyas grows a new Magisword from a tiny seed, but doesn't know that his Carnivorous Plant Magisword is a menace to Lyvsherian society until its too late!

added.title: Historias de miedo
added.description: Durante la fiesta de Halloween de la banda, iUnikitty descubre que Rick no le teme a nada! Para contagiarle el espíritu festivo, Unikitty cuenta sus propias ideas de lo que es una historia espeluznante, con la esperanza de asustar al inconmovible de Rick por una vez. iPero cada cuento es aún más espeluznante (y más tonto) que el anterior!

added.title: Haunted RV
added.description: After Uncle Grandpa's Haunted House spirals out of control, the gang must save the teenagers stuck inside.

added.title: Ya Nos Hackearon
added.description: Dendy ayuda a K.O., Enid y Rad a arreglar un problema técnico que amenaza con apoderarse de la bodega.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La noche de fiesta de los villanos
added.description: Lord Box-man entra a la fuerza en una fiesta exclusiva para villanos.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: La noche de los villanos en casa
added.description: Mientras Box-man y Venomous no están, Darrell y Shannon cuidan a Fink, aunque él no quiera.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Phased and Confused
added.description: When members of the Justice League are affected by the Phantom Zone ray and become phantom-like, their only hope for freedom is to somehow get a message to Booster Gold.

added.title: Feria de ciencias misteriosas 201x
added.description: K.O. ayuda a Dendy con su proyecto para feria de ciencias.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Unleashed
added.description: While the Justice League is away on a mission, Plastic Man is not only left in charge of the Watchtower, but also Superman's dog, Krypto.

added.title: Spooky Boo
added.description: After Clarence leads a few neighborhood kids through his homemade haunted house, Chelsea suggests they go to the high school kids haunted house for some real scares. When the gang makes a wrong turn they find themselves in a mysterious house on a hill full of creepy sounds, ghoulish shadows and mutant rat men!

added.title: Sarge esta a Cargo
added.description: Axel y el equipo deben rescatar a Sarge Charge de una misión en solitario en el patio trasero, que Orangutank ha convertido en su propio corazón personal de oscuridad.

added.title: Nocaut
added.description: Axel y el equipo hacen malabarismos sin despertar al tío Andrew de su siesta y evitar que Orangutank robe el último invento de Andrew: ila Caja Knockout!

added.title: #AmigasDelAlma Parte 1
added.description: En este episodio especial de dos partes, las chicas deben rastrear a Katana, una guerrera misteriosa que está robando las almas de los villanos de Metrópolis. Mientras tanto, Tatsu, la nueva amiga de Diana, es su alma gemela en todo sentido, ipero puede que tenga una conexión con Katana!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: #AmigasDelAlma Parte 2
added.description: En este episodio especial de dos partes, las chicas deben rastrear a Katana, una guerrera misteriosa que está robando las almas de los villanos de Metrópolis. Mientras tanto, Tatsu, la nueva amiga de Diana, es su alma gemela en todo sentido, ipero puede que tenga una conexión con Katana!
added.originalseriesname: DC Super Hero Girls en Espanol

added.title: El terror en la Montana Hook
added.description: Tigro lleva a León-O a la cima de la Montaña Hook para enseñarle una lección sobre la confianza. Pero cuando quedan atrapados por una tormenta de nieve y se refugian en una espeluznante cabaña propiedad del espeluznante Snowman, lo que se pondrá a prueba es la capacidad de Tigro para confiar.

added.title: Pantro robado
added.description: Buitro tiene un nuevo invento, pero hay un gran problema: ile robó la idea a Pantro! Ah, y además Buitro usa su invento para apoderarse del Tercer Planeta. De modo que hay dos grandes problemas.

added.title: La Venganza de Bao Bao
added.description: Cuando el antiguo compañero de Mao Mao amenaza al reino, los amigos de Mao Mao tendrán que conocer su pasado para proteger el presente.

added.title: No Me Impresiona
added.description: Cuando un Corazoncito no se siente impresionado con las hazañas del departamento del sheriff, nuestros tres héroes intentan de todo para conquistarlo.

added.title: Los Gatos Rascadores
added.description: Axel y el equipo deben ejecutar el control de daños después de que una chispa suelta de Minergy accidentalmente convierta los viejos juguetes de Zoe, un conjunto de lindos gatitos blandos, en una manada de bestias gruñendo.

added.title: La traicion
added.description: Tigro se siente poco apreciado por los demás Thundercats...i¿y por eso empieza a pasar tiempo con Mumm-Ra y a limpiar su Pirámide Negra?!

added.title: La invasion de las guerreras amazonas
added.description: El Tercer Planeta está siendo invadido por Guerreras Amazonas con fuerza y músculos extraordinarios iy parece que los Thundercats son los siguientes en su lista de ataques! Ahora, la seguridad de todos dependerá de los Thundercachorros, aunque sean tan pequeños y las Guerreras Amazonas sean tan grandes.

added.title: La Espada Perdida
added.description: A León-O le recuerdan que debe conectar la Espada del Augurio al Cubil Felino todas las noches o la base se quedará sin energía. No hay problema, no es que León-O vaya a perder accidentalmente la espada o algo así, ¿verdad?

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
added.description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

added.title: Ghost Fly
added.description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.

added.title: Sky Witch
added.description: Marceline is on a top-secret mission tracking Maja the Sky Witch. When she loses the witch's trail, Marceline turns to Princess Bubblegum for help.

added.title: Web Weirdos
added.description: When Finn gets trapped in a giant spider web, he ends up playing marriage counselor to a couple of grumpy arachnids.

added.title: Daddy's Little Monster
added.description: Finn and Jake return to the Nightosphere to rescue Marceline and get to the bottom of what's making her act so crazy.

added.title: The Monster
added.description: Lumpy Space Princess's parents have come to ask Finn and Jake to find their daughter and convince her to come home.

added.title: The Creeps
added.description: Finn and Jake receive an invitation to a masquerade dinner banquet from Count Creepystein.

added.title: From Bad to Worse
added.description: A zombie epidemic strikes in Ooo and it's Princess Bubblegum's fault.

added.title: It Came From the Nightosphere
added.description: Against Marceline's wishes, Finn conjures her father, the Lord of Evil, and attempts to reconcile their rocky relationship. But when the Lord of Evil discovers his daughter has turned the family axe into a bass guitar, he takes it from her and starts sucking up all the souls in Ooo! Finn must find a way to stop the Lord of Evil and get Marceline's guitar back.

added.title: Clarence Loves Shoopy
added.description: When Clarence discovers that one of his neighbors is the grumpy school recess proctor Ms. Shoop - he gets a glimpse of her home life and decides the only things she's missing are some friends. Clarence sets out on a mission to match the cranky oddball Shoop with some new pals!

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Puddle Eyes
added.description: A nap in mud seals Clarence's eyes and leaves him sightless, potentially dooming his team's chances in the school's ill-conceived "Vision Bee."

added.title: Nature Clarence
added.description: Clarence, Sumo and Jeff's nature hike veers off course courtesy of their under qualified, overwhelmed guide Josh, prompting Clarence to take the lead.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park VI
added.description: In Regular Show's sixth installment of "Terror Tales," the guys gather in the house on the Dome and tell scary Halloween stories just like ol' times, only this Halloween, the stories have an extra terrifying, science fiction twist.

added.title: What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

added.title: High Dive
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps Samir overcome his paralyzing fear of the high dive.

added.title: Inventor Mentor
added.description: Uncle Grandpa goes to Italy to help a young girl who wants to be a great inventor.

added.title: King Gus
added.description: Things get out of hand when Mr. Gus fulfills a timeless legend and is deemed king of the food court.

added.title: Lame Station
added.description: Pizza Steve tries desperately to make the others in the RV interested in his new game console.

added.title: Bottom Bag
added.description: After receiving a new bag friend, Belly Bag has to realize its nefarious intentions to completely replace Belly Bag and stop it before it's too late.

added.title: To Balderly Go
added.description: Prohyas is crushed when his good hair day becomes a no hair day and Vambre has to battle a furry monster alone while her bro is in shock without his locks!

added.title: Ghosthaste
added.description: Vambre becomes enamored of a poltergeist within Ghost Magisword and Prohyas must save her before his sister becomes a ghost herself!

added.title: Witchy Simone Ruins Everything!
added.description: Witchy Simone joins Witch Way, but Gateaux is the odd cat out so he hires the Warriors to break up Witchy Simone and Morbidia and defeat a mission that has King Rexxtopher hopping mad!

added.title: Transylbabies
added.description: A mission to babysit Snowmanpire babies in Transylbiria leads Vambre and Prohyas to attack the local monster townsfolk in misguided attempts to keep the Snowbabies safe.

added.title: Unconventional Dolphinism
added.description: Since Prohyas is taking Dolphin Magisword to the Dolphin Convention, Vambre asks Witchy Simone to join her on a search for the Narwhal Magisword, angering a deadly Sealdebeast guard that lures dolphins away from the convention in the process.

added.title: El Tonto
added.description: Darwin termina en la sala de detención con el Chico Bomba, que decide convertir a Darwin en su nuevo blanco. Sin embargo, el ataque se vuelve en su contra cuando Darwin le arruina la vida.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La Ficcion
added.description: Sarah encuentra un cuaderno de una tienda fabulosa, que mágicamente hace realidad lo que ella dibuja. Por desgracia, Sarah dibuja historias románticas extrañas por todo Elmore.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Historias Alternas
